Docs.summary: Represents a method within a symbol store.

remarks.format:
## Remarks The <xref:System.Diagnostics.SymbolStore.ISymbolMethod> interface provides access only to the symbol-related attributes of a method, such as sequence points, lexical scopes, and parameter information. Use it with the <xref:System.Reflection> classes to read the type-related attributes of a method.
> [!NOTE] > This interface is the managed counterpart of the `ISymUnmanagedMethod` interface, one of the unmanaged symbol store interfaces that provide an alternative way to read and write debug symbol information.

Docs.summary: Gets the sequence points for the current method.

remarks.format:
## Remarks The sequence points are sorted by offset and are for all documents in the method. Use <xref:System.Diagnostics.SymbolStore.ISymbolMethod.SequencePointCount%2A> to retrieve the count of all sequence points and create arrays of the proper size.
<xref:System.Diagnostics.SymbolStore.ISymbolMethod.GetSequencePoints%2A> verifies the size of each array and places the sequence point information into each. If any array is `null`, the data for that array is not returned.
